import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Complete Local SEO Guide for Canadian Small Businesses" description="Learn how to dominate local search results and attract more customers from your area with this comprehensive Canadian local SEO guide.">
  <article class="py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <!-- Back Link -->
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-8">
        <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400 font-medium">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"></path></svg>
          Back to Blog
        </a>
      </div>
      
      <header class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="bg-primary-100 dark:bg-primary-900/30 text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">SEO</span>
          <span class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm">15 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6">
          The Complete Local SEO Guide for Canadian Small Businesses
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
          Learn how to dominate local search results and attract more customers from your area.
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">
          <span>January 10, 2026</span>
          <span class="mx-3">â€¢</span>
          <span>Lead Flow North Team</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
          
          <p class="lead text-xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
            When someone in your city searches for your service, you want to be the first business they see. Local SEO makes that happen. This guide covers everything Canadian small businesses need to know to dominate local search.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">What is Local SEO?</h2>

          <p>
            Local SEO is the practice of optimizing your online presence to attract customers from local searches. When someone searches "plumber near me" or "best dentist in Toronto," local SEO determines which businesses appear in the results.
          </p>

          <p>
            For Canadian small businesses, local SEO is crucial because:
          </p>
          
          <ul>
            <li>46% of all Google searches have local intent</li>
            <li>88% of local mobile searches result in a call or visit within 24 hours</li>
            <li>Local searches lead to purchases 28% of the time</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Google Business Profile Optimization</h2>

          <p>
            Your Google Business Profile (formerly Google My Business) is the foundation of local SEO. It's what shows up in the "Map Pack" when people search for local services.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Essential Optimizations:</h3>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Complete every field:</strong> Name, address, phone, hours, categories, services</li>
            <li><strong>Add photos:</strong> Businesses with photos get 42% more direction requests</li>
            <li><strong>Post regularly:</strong> Weekly updates signal an active business</li>
            <li><strong>Respond to reviews:</strong> Both positive and negative, within 24-48 hours</li>
            <li><strong>Use Google Posts:</strong> Share offers, events, and updates</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">NAP Consistency</h2>

          <p>
            NAP stands for Name, Address, Phone number. Your business information must be identical everywhere it appears online. Even small differences confuse search engines.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 my-6">
            <p class="text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200 font-medium">Example of NAP inconsistency:</p>
            <ul class="text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300 mt-2">
              <li>"123 Main St" vs "123 Main Street"</li>
              <li>"Suite 100" vs "#100" vs "Ste 100"</li>
              <li>"(416) 555-1234" vs "416-555-1234"</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Local Citations</h2>

          <p>
            Citations are online mentions of your business. The more high-quality citations you have, the more Google trusts your business information.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Top Canadian Citation Sources:</h3>

          <ul>
            <li>Yellow Pages Canada</li>
            <li>Yelp Canada</li>
            <li>Canada411</li>
            <li>Canpages</li>
            <li>Industry-specific directories</li>
            <li>Local chamber of commerce</li>
            <li>Better Business Bureau</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Review Strategy</h2>

          <p>
            Reviews are one of the top ranking factors for local SEO. More importantly, they influence whether customers choose you over competitors.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">How to Get More Reviews:</h3>

          <ol>
            <li><strong>Ask at the right time:</strong> Right after a positive interaction</li>
            <li><strong>Make it easy:</strong> Send a direct link to your review page</li>
            <li><strong>Follow up:</strong> A gentle reminder increases completion rates</li>
            <li><strong>Respond to all reviews:</strong> Shows you value customer feedback</li>
          </ol>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Local Content Strategy</h2>

          <p>
            Creating content that targets local keywords helps you rank for more searches. Think about what your local customers are searching for.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Local Content Ideas:</h3>

          <ul>
            <li>City-specific service pages (e.g., "Plumbing Services in Mississauga")</li>
            <li>Local guides and resources</li>
            <li>Community involvement and events</li>
            <li>Local case studies and testimonials</li>
            <li>Answers to local-specific questions</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Mobile Optimization</h2>

          <p>
            Most local searches happen on mobile devices. If your website isn't mobile-friendly, you're losing customers.
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Fast loading:</strong> Under 3 seconds on mobile</li>
            <li><strong>Click-to-call buttons:</strong> Make it easy to contact you</li>
            <li><strong>Easy navigation:</strong> Large buttons, readable text</li>
            <li><strong>Local schema markup:</strong> Help search engines understand your business</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Tracking Your Progress</h2>

          <p>
            Monitor these metrics to measure your local SEO success:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>Google Business Profile views and actions</li>
            <li>Local pack rankings for target keywords</li>
            <li>Website traffic from local searches</li>
            <li>Phone calls and direction requests</li>
            <li>Review quantity and average rating</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-600 to-primary-700 p-8 rounded-xl text-white my-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Need Help With Local SEO?</h3>
            <p class="text-primary-100 mb-6">
              Get a free local SEO audit and see exactly where your business can improve. We'll show you quick wins and long-term strategies.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center bg-white text-primary-600 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-primary-50 transition">
              Get Your Free Audit
            </a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
